<% title 'Safety concerns' %>

<div class="grid-row">
  <div class="column-two-thirds">
    <%= step_header %>
    <div class="grid_content_header">
      <h1 class="heading-xlarge gv-u-heading-xxlarge">Safety concerns</h1>
    </div>

    <div class=" govuk-govspeak gv-s-prose">
      <p>The court needs to know if the other person (the respondent) or anyone they're in contact with poses a risk to the safety of you or your children.</p>
      <div role="note" aria-label="Information" class=" panel panel-border-wide info-notice TODO"><p>We use ‘children’ as a general term to avoid repetition. In this service it applies to whether you have a child or children.</p>
      </div>
      <p>The following questions will ask whether you or your children have experienced, or are at risk of experiencing,
        any form of harm.</p>
      <p>Find out about the
        <a href="https://www.nspcc.org.uk/preventing-abuse/child-abuse-and-neglect/" target="external_link">signs of
          child abuse</a> and
        <a href="http://www.refuge.org.uk/get-help-now/help-for-women/recognising-abuse/" target="external_link">domestic
          abuse</a>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="xform-group form-submit">
      <%= link_to 'Continue', edit_steps_safety_questions_address_confidentiality_path, class: 'button', role: 'button' %>
    </div>
    <div class="extraBlocks  govuk-govspeak gv-s-prose">
      <div>
        <details role="group" data-block-name="safety-concerns-reasons">
          <summary role="button">
            <span class="summary">Why do we need to ask this?</span>
          </summary>
          <div class=" panel panel-border-narrow undefined">
            <p>An advisor from the <a href="https://www.cafcass.gov.uk/">Children and Family Court Advisory and Support Service (<abbr title="Children and Family Court Advisory and Support Service">Cafcass</abbr>)</a> or <a href="http://cafcass.gov.wales/">CAFCASS Cymru</a> will look at your answers as part of their background checks.</p>
            <p><abbr title="Children and Family Court Advisory and Support Service">Cafcass</abbr> and CAFCASS Cymru protect the interests of children involved in family court cases.</p>
            <p>The advisor will also contact organisations such as the police and local authorities to see if they have any information about you, the other person or your children.</p>
            <p>They then submit a report to the court before your first hearing. Their findings help the judge make a decision that is in the best interests of your children.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
